{"title_page": "List of Esperanto-language writers", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nAuthors from many nations have written [[Esperanto literature|literature]] in the [[Esperanto]] language, a [[constructed language|constructed]] [[international auxiliary language]] with an estimated two million speakers worldwide.<ref name=\"e18\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/epo|title=Esperanto|accessdate=6 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Alphabetical list of notable authors==\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|- valign=top\n|width=\"25%\" |\n\n===A===\n*[[Hendrik Adamson]], poet\n*[[Teresa de Almeida]] (1932\u2013 ), poet \n*[[Nadija Hordijenko Andrianova]] (1928\u20131991), writer\n*[[William Auld]]\n\n===B===\n*[[Julio Baghy]], novelist\n*[[Claude Piron|Joh\u00e1n Balano]]\n*[[Gerrit Berveling]]\n*[[Marjorie Boulton]] \n*[[Hendrik Bulthuis]]\n\n===C===\n*[[Jorge Camacho (writer)|Jorge Camacho]] \n*[[Claudius Colas]]\n\n===D===\n*[[Teresa de Almeida|Vimala Devi (Teresa de Almeida)]] \n*[[Frans van Dooren]]\n*[[Deck Dorval]]\n\n===F===\n*[[Jean Forge]]\n*[[Edmund Edward Fournier d'Albe]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dib.cambridge.org/viewReadPage.do?articleId=a9268&searchClicked=clicked&searchBy=1&browsesearch=yes|title=Dictionary of Irish Biography \u2013 Cambridge University Press|website=dib.cambridge.org|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ainm.ie/Bio.aspx?ID=254|title=FOURNIER D'ALBE, Edmund Edward (1868\u20131933)|website=ainm.ie|language=ga|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref>\n*[[Jan Filip (priest)|Jan Filip]]\n\n===G===\n*[[Antoni Grabowski]]\n\n|width=\"25%\" |\n\n===H===\n*[[Marie Hankel]]\n\n===I===\n*[[Saburo Ito]]\n*[[Vsevolod Ivanov]]\n\n===K===\n*[[K\u00e1lm\u00e1n Kalocsay]]\n\n===L===\n*[[Georges Lagrange]]\n*[[Jonathan Leunbach]] \n*[[Anna L\u00f6wenstein]]\n\n===M===\n*[[Abel Montagut]]\n\n===N===\n*[[Ivan Naumov]]\n*[[Istv\u00e1n Nemere]]\n\n|width=\"25%\" |\n\n===P===\n*[[Edward Saxton Payson]] (1842\u20131932)\n