{"title_page": "Mol language", "text_new": "{{Infobox language\n|name=Amol\n|nativename=''Alatil''\n|states=[[Papua New Guinea]]\n|region=[[Sandaun Province]]\n|speakers=270\n|date=2000 census\n|ref=e18\n|familycolor=Papuan\n|fam1=[[Torricelli languages|Torricelli]]\n|fam2=[[Palei languages|Palei]]\n|iso3=alx\n|glotto=amol1235\n|glottorefname=Mol\n}}\n\n'''Amol''', also '''Alatil''' or '''Aru''', is a [[Torricelli languages|Torricelli language]] of [[Papua New Guinea]].  The names '''Amol''' and '''Aru''' are both slightly erroneous.  Speakers of the language call their language '''Mol''' (not '''Amol'''), while speakers of surrounding languages call the language '''Oru''' (not '''Aru''').  [[Matthew S. Dryer]] of the University at Buffalo has collected data on Mol.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Torricelli languages}}\n{{Languages of Papua New Guinea}}\n\n[[Category:Palei languages]]\n[[Category:Languages of Papua New Guinea]]\n[[Category:Languages of Sandaun Province]]\n\n{{papuan-lang-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox language\n|name=Amol\n|nativename=Alatil\n|states=[[Papua New Guinea]]\n|region=[[Sandaun Province]]\n|speakers=270\n|date=2000 census\n|ref=e18\n|familycolor=Papuan\n|fam1=[[Torricelli languages|Torricelli]]\n|fam2=[[Palei languages|Palei]]\n|iso3=alx\n|glotto=amol1235\n|glottorefname=Mol\n}}\n\n'''Amol''', also '''Alatil''' or '''Aru''', is a [[Torricelli languages|Torricelli language]] of [[Papua New Guinea]].  The names '''Amol''' and '''Aru''' are both slightly erroneous.  Speakers of the language call their language '''Mol''' (not '''Amol'''), while speakers of surrounding languages call the language '''Oru''' (not '''Aru''').  [[Matthew S. Dryer]] of the University at Buffalo has collected data on Mol.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Torricelli languages}}\n{{Languages of Papua New Guinea}}\n\n[[Category:Palei languages]]\n[[Category:Languages of Papua New Guinea]]\n[[Category:Languages of Sandaun Province]]\n\n{{papuan-lang-stub}}\n